caption: Delicious empanadas! Highly recommend the pastor and spinach! And the staff are super friendly :)
Best empanadas I’ve had in a very long time! They come with amazing sauces, and the staff were so nice and helpful! Will be coming here way more often
The best empanadas
Best mexican empanadas ever!!!
I had the al pastor, beef and rice, and Champion chicken. All excellent! Would reccomend.
Cheap food and fast service plus delicious empanadas = I'm going back tomorrow
Love all the different flavors they offer. There's so much variety here and I know I'll be coming back for more. This just became a habit!
The empanadas are delicious and the staff are delightful!
really good!
These empanadas were so tasty!! #6 was my favorite. Staff was so friendly and the food came out quickly, was also reasonably priced. Perfect for our Saturday afternoon snack. Menu attached!
Stopped here for a little snack on a cold shopping day in LP. We ordered a #2 and a #6. They were so good we immediately ordered two more. I highly recommend stopping in 👌🏼.

Have been here twice.  Flavorful empanadas that are made in house. Would recommend the savory ones, especially the chorizo one. The desert ones , like the apple pie, are not worth it. Seating is limited in the store so be ready to cozy up with other diners.
My meal was fast and the price was very economical. Fast, effective service with a very friendly staff. Highly Recommended. Best Empanadas in Chicago!
Great service, great food!
Loved seeing the empanada machine.
Literally the best thing I've ever put in my mouth.
Amazing food and an amazing chef. Cute little seating area makes it really cozy
OMG SOOOO DELICIOUS!!!
(Translated by Google) Empanadas made instantly, very delicious.  (Original) Empanadas hechas al instante, muy deliciosas.
Delicious
Had the # 4 and #12! First time coming here. For the price, it’s unbeatable. Filling, tasty, and comforting. Cashier was also nice and good with customers 👍🏻
Delicious!
Great prices for what you get. There is a big selection of fillings for the empanadas.
Absolutely fantastic empanadas. Can't recommend em enough. I always bring my friends here for a good quick cheap bite.

Great empanadas! Not much in the way of a store, you just pretty much walk right into the kitchen once you're in the door. But the empanadas are bigger and better than that fancier empanada joint down the street.
A little small, but very quick in-and-out. All their empanadas were delicious and reasonably priced. The gentleman working there was extremely friendly.
Delicious! And great options for vegans and vegetarians!
Always tasty!
I tried the Hawaiian & chicken bbq empanada. I enjoyed both very much. They also offer sweet options such as caramel apple and more.

Great food and atmosphere. I was greeted by a beautiful young African girl, so full of life and spirit. She took my order making me feel at home. Service exquisite, food incredible, and at a great price. Definitely will be back😆

I had the BEST empanada I have ever had. I only ate one (Spinach and cheese), but that was enough! Staff was friendly and funny and I didn't wait too long! I was hoping that they were not closed on the 4th when I went there...I am happy they were not.

I absolutely love this place - their empanadas are really good and they're pretty quick at making them. I haven't had any issue ordering from them, except once when they missed my order and they were very apologetic. I would definitely recommend this place if you like empanadas! Especially ones that are more atypical
Mouth watering empanadas!! Friendly service and reasonable prices
Best place for empanadas
The very best!!!!!!!! Drive from Ohio just for them
Never a disappointment, always delicious!

Went to Lito's on a whim tonight. This was my first time there. My friend had the spinach, we shared the chicken and I had the chorizo!! They were all DELICIOUS! Service was fast. We will both be going back.
Amazing empanadas. Realky cozy place
Their empanadas are delicious. I loved the idea that they have aji and pink sauce! Sauces to put in the empanadas that are very common in latino countries. Loved them!
Their eclectic selection of empanadas were tasty and authentic. The location itself was somewhat small but not terribly busy when friends and I went there in the afternoon.
Ordered the beef #1 empanada. Easily the best empanada I've had in the city as the dough and meat tasted very fresh. Good price point as well given the area.
Small place but very authentic yummy empanadas. They are pretty chunky so if you want to try several consider splitting with others.  My fav had chorizo 😋. The sauces are amazing too!
The best empanadas in Chicago. It's  a take out place basically few seats at the window but the empanadas are perfect especially the Champion Chicken and the Apple!

Mmmm, these empanadas were the best I’ve ever had! You have to wait a few minutes for the cook, but I was happy to. I had 3 of them, but 2 would have been enough. The price is right and the taste is out of this world!
Really good. Better than 5411. Good sized. Eat the Al pastor for sure.
Lito's has great empanadas. We travel all the way from the far southwest side to Lito's because they are so good. I like the beef and rice and my daughter likes the bbq chicken. So good.
Yummy! I love these empanadas. They even have a veggie one!
Really really doughy. Also, I got the champinon chicken and couldn't find any mushrooms in it.
The empanadas are delicious and a great portion size.
I’ve has the chicken, beef with rice, and apple cinnamon empanadas. They were delicious. Definitely going back!
So yum!!!

Great empanadas..i have tried the chori-cheese, beef and rice, spinach, and the champiñon chicken which is my favorite. You do wait a bit for your order but it is worth it..and that pink sauce compliments the empanadas very well.

This place is awesome! I got the cheese and spinach (I can't remember the exact name of it) empanada and it was SO good. I've had my eye on this place for almost a year and was so pleased after I finally went. I thought the service was good as well; very quick.

Great food. Tasty and filling. The cashier was not customer oriented. Very dry personality and lacked information about the business and surrounding area. She also, did not take our order correctly. I won't penalize the restaurant for her behavior. She could easily be spoken with and add some spunk and customer service to her personality
What a wonderful place. Is small but the emapanadas in there are the best that I had from Chicago just like in Colombia ❤️. The workers in there are nice too !!
Empanadas are very good,  the only thing is they don't have restrooms for their customers ☹
Delicious empanadas! Great for take out as they have a small place for eating in.
Love the spinach empanada, read the menu
Amazing food and great prices!

Empanadas here were so good; right amount of crispiness on the outside and savory flavor (I ordered four different kinds) on the inside. Highly recommended to try their sauces; goes real well together! Makes me want to go there now to grab some.
The best empanadas in Chicago
Small meat pie + green chillies sauce = party in your mouth
Best empanadas in Chicago
Soooo tasty!

Love when a place sucks to what they're great at. Lito's has fantastic empanadas, and the only other thing you can get here is a bottle drink. The empanadas were fresh, delicious, and economical ($3/each). Highly recommend this place for a quick bite.
Great food, friendly service! Usually not very crowded but there aren't many seats so keep that in mind if you're there with a big group
I've ordered from them pretty frequently and never had any problems! Staff always friendly and extremely helpful ! Empanadas always hot and really good !!
I've never been disappointed when I order from these friendly people😊
Delicious, had the chorizo one.
Affordable and super tasty
(Translated by Google) I recommend the sausage pawned.  (Original) I recommend the chorizo empeñada.

Best empanadas I've ever had. All they have is empanadas so they definitely know how to make a killer empanada. Quick if you're in a hurry. It is a tiny place thou so I wouldn't go there with a large group.
Amazing. Deliver furthur please!
Fantastic empanadas. I've had a slew of empanadas in Ecuador and these are even better.
the taste is a journey to another world. crispy, filled and fried to perfection. must try.

Need a quick fix for that nagging hunger?  Lito's has you covered!  A delicious empanada will take 5-7 minutes to come out piping hot but the wait is worth it.  You won't find much seating or comfort but this place turns out some great empanadas.  Want something else?  Go somewhere else.  This place does one thing and does it amazing.
Amazing empanadas!
So delicious

Went here this past weekend for a quick bite.  I ordered the chicken with rice, beef, and banana/chocolate empanadas.  They were really delicious!  I thought that I was not going to like the beef because it had olives in it, but it was very good.  They came to me hot and not greasy at all.  I was also surprised by the banana and chocolate empanada....not your typical empanada, but it was great!  When I come back, I"ll definitely try the rest.
The best empanadas in Chicago!  I've tried almost everything on the menu but love the Chicken Champinon. You can also buy them frozen and make them at home.
A really nice hole in the wall feeling place that serves pretty delicious empanadas ranging from super savory to sweet desserts. Not the healthiest but definitely tasty.
empanadas are just ok, they can be a hit or miss.  The banana nutella is great though. Homemade hot sauce is fresh and delicious.  Friendly service!

i had the spinach and bbq empanadas...they were the best i ever i had. i even drank the hot sauce out the container. I love family-owned spots like this and i can tell the cook was a cool dude..he gave a nice warm smile..im going back again today!

Hawaiin empanadas. Chicken empanadas. Beef empanadas. Banana nutella emapanadas for dessert. That's a full meal! Love this place, super cheap. Order them for take-out when you want a good meal and don't feel like cooking. 2 per person always fills the family up. Again, great prices for the food you get. Reccommend!
Excellent empanadas!  Spinach and cheese is by far the best one.  The pink sauce for dipping is a great addition.

For under 5 bucks, it's possible to get full off of 2 empanadas.  They are decently sized, and very filling.  Perfect for lunch if you are on-the-go and great as a picnic food with a six pack of beer.  My favorites include the Hawaiian and the BBQ chicken.  The chocolate-banana is wonderful, but make sure you heat it back up in the oven if you take it to-go.  The chocolate has to ooze out in order to be good.
Absoutly love this place. Fast inexpensive snack always good and a good assortment of choices. I just wish there was one near where I live by O'hare
Where else can you get fast empanadas? Well made, cheap, and quick.
Nice variety. Delicious empanadas.
(Translated by Google) yummmmmy  (Original) Yummmmmy
Empanadas are the only thing on the menu, but they're quite tasty.  Very little seating space - only a few stools at the window counter - so go when it's not crowded, or plan to pick up and go.
